<!doctype html>
<!--
  adopter-welcome.step-7.mjml — Month 4: called to be faithful.
  Source: Drip Emails for adopter Sign-up.docx (Email 8).
-->
<html><body style="font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; color: #1f2937;">
  <h2 style="color: #1f2937;">Called to be Faithful</h2>
  <p>Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>

  <p>
    Today you have been praying for your adopted people group for over
    three months! Yet, the work has just begun. Though the challenges of
    reaching those who have had little to no response to the Gospel are
    great, we serve our great God who is faithful.
  </p>

  <p>
    We here at Joshua Project see every day how the body of Christ is
    working together to make Him known in some of the hardest places on
    earth. For those who labor in this, we want to remind you that you are
    not alone. We join together in prayer for these FPGs.
  </p>

  <p>
    As we all seek to be faithful to the commitment of FPG Adoption, a bit
    of encouragement may be in order. The Light the Nations prayer map is a
    prayer tool that is helpful for prayer networks and others who want to
    pray broadly for the people groups of the world. By entering the map,
    the person can look for FPGs around the world (the dark dots on the
    map). As each FPG is prayed for, their dot will light up for 24 hours.
    This interactive tool allows us to see and share the need for prayer
    for the FPGs around the globe.
  </p>

  <p>
    The process of reaching an FPG is a marathon. There are bound to be
    times of great activity and times of waiting upon the Lord. As you go
    through this process, Joshua Project will be updating additional
    resources for you to help refresh and refocus you or your group. The
    <em>FPG Adoption Resources</em> are here for you.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our prayer for you is that the challenges of the hard work of seeing
    Frontier Peoples reached with the gospel will strengthen your faith in
    the toils and help each of us realize that God is the one who determines
    the outcomes. We continue in faithful efforts together, while our hope
    is in our God who is faithful.
  </p>

  <p>Many blessings,<br/>The Joshua Project Team</p>
  <p style="color: #6b7280; font-style: italic;">
    "Now may the God of peace Himself sanctify you completely; and may your
    whole spirit, soul, and body be preserved blameless at the coming of our
    Lord Jesus Christ. He who calls you is faithful, who also will do it."
    (1 Thessalonians 5:23-24 NIV)
  </p>

  <p style="color: #9ca3af; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 32px;">
    Reply "unsubscribe" to stop receiving this series.
  </p>
</body></html>
